# gitkit

Read-only repo-analysis toolkit — point luxe at an existing git repo and get a
packaged markdown report. Three kinds: `gitsummary` (project / deps / health /
use-risk verdict — SINGLE-PASS only), `gitreview` (serious bug & security
findings), `gitrefactor` (ordered structural refactor plan). Additive front-end;
reuses `run_single`, the read-only tool surface, and the prompt registry's
existing overlays.

> [!IMPORTANT]
> The repository summary is FOLDED IN: `gitreview`/`gitrefactor` reports begin
> (after their title + count line) with a `## Repository summary & risk` section,
> derived from the shared survey + health data they already gather. `gitsummary`
> remains a thin, SINGLE-PASS command for that orientation alone — it never runs
> the deep map-reduce (no `GIT_SUMMARY_CHUNK_HINT`/`GIT_SUMMARY_SYNTH_HINT`).
> `gitrefactor` additionally consumes a prior same-commit `gitreview`'s findings
> (injected as a `<prior_findings>` data block) so its steps don't undo fixes.

Exposed two ways: `luxe gitsummary|gitreview|gitrefactor <repo>` (+ aliases
git-summary/gsum, git-review/grev, git-refactor/gref) over an arbitrary local
path or git URL; and `/gitsummary|/gitreview|/gitrefactor` in `luxe chat` over
the session's pinned repo.

For large repos a STAGED DEEP MODE (gitkit/deep.py) replaces the single pass: the
runner orchestrates multiple sequential read-only `run_single` passes (survey →
plan/chunk → per-chunk notes → synthesis) in Python — the `compare/run_pair.py`
front-end-orchestration precedent, NOT the retired in-agent swarm/phased modes.
Each pass is still ONE mono call with no in-agent repair loop; the staging lives
in the front-end. Survey map + chunk plan persist per repo under
`~/.luxe/reports/<repo_hash>/map/` (HEAD-keyed); per-run notes under a sibling
`<kind>-<ts>-<rand>.work/`.

## Must
- Be AGENT-READ-ONLY: the ANALYSIS runs through `make_read_only_role`
  (mcp/server.py) — the model's tools cannot write/edit the repo (no `/write`).
  Canonical report/map/notes live under `~/.luxe/reports/`, written by the
  ORCHESTRATOR (plain Python), never by an agent tool.
  > [!IMPORTANT]
  > One SANCTIONED orchestrator write into the target repo: a committable
  > `<repo>/.luxe/gitkit/` MIRROR (survey map + the latest report + a generated
  > `README.md` marker), default-on, `--no-mirror` to skip — `store.mirror_to_repo`,
  > plain Python, NEVER via an agent tool, touching ONLY the `.luxe/gitkit/`
  > sidecar (never source). Mirrors the `.luxe/memory.md` precedent. Best-effort:
  > a filesystem error is swallowed, never aborting the analysis.
- The `gitplan` ANALYSIS is read-only like every other kind (runs through
  `make_read_only_role`; emits a structured `plan-<head>.json` + the markdown report,
  both under `~/.luxe/reports/` + mirrored; never edits source).
  > [!IMPORTANT]
  > `gitplan --apply` / `luxe gitapply` is the SOLE SANCTIONED AGENT-WRITE PATH in
  > gitkit (`gitkit/apply.py`). It runs the agent in WRITE mode (the FULL role, NOT
  > `make_read_only_role`) under SIX mandatory invariants, every one enforced:
  > 1. INTERACTIVE-ONLY — requires a TTY; no TTY ⇒ abort. Applying unattended is
  >    forbidden; the sweep NEVER applies.
  > 2. CLEAN-TREE-ONLY — aborts if the working tree is dirty (no `--allow-dirty`).
  > 3. NON-DEFAULT-BRANCH — never main/master/the detected default branch; always a
  >    dedicated `gitplan/<head>-<rand>` branch (created up front).
  > 4. PER-STEP GATING — one MONO `run_single` per ordered step; after each, capture
  >    the diff, run the step's `verify`, SHOW both, and require an interactive
  >    keep|discard. `keep` commits on the branch; `discard` reverts only that step.
  >    `depends_on` is honored (a dependent is skipped if its prerequisite wasn't kept).
  > 5. NEVER pushes, NEVER merges, NEVER commits to the default branch, NEVER touches
  >    files outside the working tree.
  > 6. Orchestration is front-end Python (the deep.py/compare precedent): multiple
  >    mono passes, each ONE call, NO in-agent repair loop / goal-runner / retry.
- Pick the path by repo size: small/medium repos → SINGLE-PASS (exactly one
  `run_single`, unchanged); large repos (estimated token footprint over the deep
  threshold, or `--deep`/`/gitreview deep`) → the staged deep mode above. The
  decision is `deep.should_use_deep` (footprint-primary; file/symbol counts are
  NOT the gate). `--no-deep`/`shallow` forces single-pass. `gitsummary` is ALWAYS
  single-pass (it never enters deep mode regardless of size). Neither path runs an
  in-agent repair/iteration loop or a goal-runner.
- Inject git-health + GitHub metadata, the repo map, survey notes, the chunk file
  list, and the cross-reference digest ONLY as data via `run_single`'s
  `extra_context`, tagged (`<repo_health>` / `<github_metadata>` / `<repo_map>` /
  `<framing_files>` / `<survey_notes>` / `<chunk_files>` / `<cross_reference_digest>`
  / `<chunk_findings>`). Every block is pure data and must carry no
  instruction-like text.
- Gather GitHub data out-of-band through the `gh` CLI in `health.py`, never by
  adding `gh` to the shared bash allowlist (tools/shell.py `_ALLOWLIST` is the
  benchmark tool surface). All `gh` calls go through one helper that degrades
  gracefully (gh missing / unauthenticated / non-GitHub remote / timeout / empty
  repo) to a single-line placeholder; the report still renders from local git.
- Map each kind to an EXISTING task_type/overlay (gitsummary→summarize,
  gitreview/gitrefactor/gitplan→review; the apply step→implement). The per-kind
  directive rides in the `goal` via a `*_HINT` constant from `agents/prompts.py` —
  no new task types, no prompt-registry churn.
- Save reports to `~/.luxe/reports/<repo_hash>/<kind>-<ts>-<rand>.md` (always
  `mkdir(parents=True, exist_ok=True)`; `repo_hash` from memory/project.py). Deep
  mode additionally persists `map/` (HEAD-keyed survey + chunk plan) and
  `<kind>-<ts>-<rand>.work/` (per-chunk notes + `xref.json`) under the same dir.
- Deep mode reuses the cached `map/` when HEAD matches (skip survey + chunk
  rebuild); invalidate on HEAD move or `--rebuild-map`. Map is kind-agnostic
  (survey + chunking shared); only per-chunk + synthesis are per-kind.
- CLI targets an arbitrary repo; REPL analyzes ONLY `session.repo_path` (reusing
  the session's resident indices) and warns if HEAD moved since indices built.
- Keep the benchmark/maintain path byte-identical: deep mode is front-end only
  (cli/chat → runner → deep); `single.py`/`loop.py`/benchmarks never reach it.

## Must not
- Write/edit the target repo, or require write mode — EXCEPT the `gitplan --apply`
  path, which is write-enabled under its six invariants above. Every other path (all
  kinds, incl. `gitplan` WITHOUT `--apply`) stays agent-read-only.
- Add tools to the shared bash allowlist, or mutate `run_single`/`run_agent`
  signatures (deep mode + the apply executor call `run_single` with its existing
  public params only).
- Read `~/.claude/` or the repo-root `CLAUDE.md`.
- Run an in-AGENT repair/iteration loop or goal-runner in ANY path. (Deep mode AND
  the apply executor orchestrate multiple mono passes from the front-end; that is
  allowed and is not a per-agent loop. Do not "optimize" a single pass into a
  mini-maintain workflow, and the apply executor must NOT retry a step's pass.)
- Silently cap coverage: a `--max-chunks` truncation must `log` what was dropped.

## Owns
- src/luxe/gitkit/** (incl. `plan.py` — plan JSON parse/normalize/render/save —
  and `apply.py` — the gated executor)

## Forbids
- Prompt/directive strings here — they live in `agents/prompts.py`
  (single-pass: `GIT_SUMMARY_HINT` / `GIT_REVIEW_HINT` / `GIT_REFACTOR_HINT` /
  `GIT_PLAN_HINT`; deep: `GIT_SURVEY_HINT`, `GIT_*_CHUNK_HINT`, `GIT_*_SYNTH_HINT`,
  `GIT_DEEP_REDUCE_HINT`; apply: `GIT_APPLY_STEP_HINT`). `plan.py`/`apply.py` hold
  only orchestration + deterministic data shaping (parse/normalize/render, git ops,
  the keep/discard gate).
